    "Our implementation of the Von Neumann extractor has a computation time of O(n 1), while Trevisan has a computation time of O n 1 m log 2 n 1 m ϵ.",
    "A simple user's guideTo help using Cryptomite, Figure 2 presents a flowchart which assists a user on deciding which extractor to use for their application and Figure 3 summarises the achievable parameters.",
    "The flowchart is somewhat informal and one can obtain small improvements by analysing each extractor individually (for example, finding a slightly longer output length or shorter seed length).",
    "The objective is to give a simple yet good choice for any application, in a clear and easy to follow diagram.",
    "In this guide, the user begins with some extractor input of length n 1 and min-entropy k 1 (Definition 1)."
